# Architecture

## The pipeline (one-way)

```
market_data → feature_engineering → signal_models → strategy_engine
            → risk_engine → execution → monitoring
```

Each stage is one Python package. Cross-stage shortcuts are forbidden.

## Module ownership (no upstream imports)

| Stage              | Package         | May import from                        |
|--------------------|-----------------|----------------------------------------|
| market_data        | `data/`         | (stdlib + pandas + duckdb)             |
| feature_engineering| `research/features/` | `data/`                          |
| signal_models      | `research/models/` | `research/features/`, `data/`      |
| strategy_engine    | `strategies/`   | `research/`, `data/`                   |
| risk_engine        | `risk/`         | `strategies/`, `data/`                 |
| execution          | `execution/`    | `strategies/`, `risk/`, `data/`        |
| monitoring         | `monitoring/`   | any (pure observer)                    |

`execution/` MUST NOT import `research.llm` (LLM isolation; CI-enforced in
`tests/security/test_llm_isolation.py`).

## The only path to a placed order

```
Strategy.target_positions(state)
  → RiskEngine.check_and_size(orders, portfolio)
    → Broker.place_order(order)
```

There is no other path. Adding one is a release blocker.

## Interfaces are typed contracts

- Stages communicate via Pydantic models / dataclasses, not raw dicts.
- Money is `Decimal` at any broker boundary; floats inside research only.
- Timestamps are timezone-aware `pd.Timestamp(tz="UTC")`.
- Configs are YAML in `configs/`, loaded via Pydantic models.

